// Auto-generated from Python source: 2026-07-17
// 3-bit trigrams × 3-bit trigrams × 3-bit phase = 9-bit encoding
// 64 hexagrams × 8 phases = 512 total entries
//
// Each line is ternary: 0=yin, 1=yang, 2=yao (changing)
// 6 ternary lines = 3^6 = 729 possible line-state combinations
// Base states (no yao): 2^6 = 64 hexagrams
//
// Phase bits control which lines become yao:
//   bit 0 -> lines 1, 4 (position 1 in lower/upper trigrams)
//   bit 1 -> lines 2, 5 (position 2 in lower/upper trigrams)
//   bit 2 -> lines 3, 6 (position 3 in lower/upper trigrams)
// ============================================================================

